const libraryData = {"App_Walkthrough": "# Walkthrough: Chess Command Center - Elite 12-Month Mastery\n\nI have completed the final polish of your **Chess Command Center**. The application is now a \"world-class\" interactive dashboard, designed to keep you motivated and disciplined on your journey to 2400 FIDE.\n\n## \ud83c\udf1f Premium Visual Overhaul\n\nYour dashboard has been transformed with a modern, high-end \"Elite Mastery\" aesthetic:\n\n- **Dynamic Mesh Background**: A subtle, animated gradient that gives the app a living, breathing feel without distracting from your study.\n- **\"Shining\" Header**: The \"Chess Command Center\" title now features a metallic shine effect that pulses with light.\n- **Enhanced Glassmorphism**: Cards now have higher blur values (`20px`), smoother borders, and deep shadows, making them feel like premium physical objects on a digital screen.\n- **Entry Animations**: Every element staggers into view when you switch months, creating a \"Mission Start\" feeling every time you navigate.\n\n## \ud83c\udfc6 Daily Positivity & Rewards\n\nI have expanded the app to make your daily progress uplifting:\n\n- **Everyday Fresh Start**: The Command Center acts as your daily dashboard. See exactly what you need to do, gaze at the course poster, and jump straight into work.\n- **Positivity Quotes**: As you check off tasks, you are greeted with positive quotes and encouragement to recognize your hard work.\n- **Milestone Rewards**: Completing your monthly curriculum triggers a congratulatory overlay, spreading positivity and recognizing your dedication.\n- **The Final Ascension**: Finishing Month 12 signifies the culmination of your consistent daily effort!\n\n## \ud83d\udccb Content Integrity\n\n- **High-Impact \"Jobs\"**: Every month now features a clearly defined \"Daily Job\" (e.g., \"Eliminate all 1-move blunders\").\n- **Direct Chessable Links**: All \"Open Course\" buttons link directly to the premium materials planned for your curriculum.\n- **Elite Superpowers**: Each phase of the 12-month plan highlights the specific skill (Superpower) you are unlocking.\n\n## \ud83d\ude80 How to Launch\n\n1. Open `index.html` in any modern web browser.\n2. Navigate through the 1\u201312 timeline to see your full curriculum.\n3. Check off tasks as you complete them to gain \"Monthly Strength.\"\n\nYour Command Center is ready. The path to 2400 starts today.\n", "chessable_author_analysis": "# Chessable Author & Course Deep Analysis\n## For 1773 \u2192 2400 Journey (2026)\n\n---\n\n## CAN KABADAYI \u2014 Full Catalog Analysis\n*2024 Chessable Author of the Year | FIDE Instructor | Cognitive Science background*\n\n| Course | Verdict | Fit for Plan |\n|--------|---------|--------------|\n| **Preventing Blunders** | **BUY** | Month 1 supplement |\n| **The Value of Pawns** | **BUY** | Month 4 supplement |\n| **Chess Crime and Punishment** | **BUY** | Month 6 supplement |\n| **Piece Coordination Trilogy** | **BUY** | Month 7 primary |\n| **Art of Multi-Purpose Moves** | **BUY** | Month 10 supplement |\n\n---\n\n## GM RAMESH RB \u2014 The \"Process\" Master\n*Coach of Pragg, Gukesh | Author of \"Improve Your Chess Calculation\"*\n\n| Course | Verdict |\n|--------|---------|\n| **Improve Your Chess Calculation** | \u2705 **SENSATIONAL (Month 9)** |\n\n---\n\n## GM PETER HEINE NIELSEN (P.H.N.)\n- **Verdict**: **ESSENTIAL CORE (Month 4)**. \n- **Course**: *Chess Structures - A Grandmaster Guide (Video)*.\n- **Why**: Coached Magnus Carlsen; translates engine analysis into human plans.\n\n---\n\n## GM BORIS GELFAND\n- **Verdict**: **THE FINAL BOSS (Month 10 & 12)**.\n- **Course**: *Positional Decision Making*; *Dynamic Decision Making*.\n\n---\n\n## THE \"ELITE\" TRACK SUMMARY\n1. **Month 1**: Technique (Ninja) \u2192 Volume (Woodpecker) \u2192 Safety (Kabadayi).\n2. **Month 3**: Process (Ramesh) \u2192 Structural Plans (Flores).\n3. **Month 7**: Coordination (Kabadayi Trilogy).\n4. **Month 9-12**: Deep Calculation (Aagaard) \u2192 Elite Decision Making (Gelfand).\n", "chess_improvement_plan": "# \u265f\ufe0f Chess Improvement Plan (2026): 1773 \u2192 2400\n\n**Starting Rating:** ~1773 OTB  \n**Target:** 2400 FIDE (IM norm threshold)  \n**Rule:** Play \u2192 Analyze \u2192 Identify Weakness \u2192 Study \u2192 Repeat\n\n---\n\n## Opening Repertoire\n\n| Color | Situation | Course / Resource |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **White** | 1. f4 (Bird) | *Lifetime Repertoires: Bird's Opening* (Chessable) |\n| **Black vs 1.e4** | 1\u2026e5 | *Lifetime Repertoires: 1\u2026e5* \u2014 Gawain Jones |\n| **Black vs 1.d4** | Benko Gambit | *Benko Gambit Blueprint* (Chessable) |\n| **Black vs 1.c4** | Reversed Sicilian | *The Reversed Sicilian* \u2014 Artur Neiksans |\n\n> [!NOTE]\n> **Repertoire Choice:** We are staying with **Bird's Opening (1.f4)** for efficiency. 1.e4 with the Scotch is high-maintenance (requires 5+ extra courses for Sicilian/Caro/etc). If you *must* play 1.e4, use the **King's Indian Attack (KIA)** against all non-1...e5 lines (e.g., Simon Williams - Modern Reti principles).\n\n> [!IMPORTANT]\n> Learn openings **only to the depth needed for your rating now**. Deep memorization before understanding is wasted effort. Focus on ideas and typical plans until Month 9+.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1 \u2014 Foundation (Months 1\u20133)\n\n### Month 1: Tactical Foundation (Ninja + Woodpecker + Kabadayi Blunders)\n**Opening Work (light):**\n- *Bird's Opening* LTR \u2014 Chapters 1\u20136 (main 1.f4 e5 and 1.f4 d5 lines)\n- *1\u2026e5* Jones LTR \u2014 Chapters 1\u20134 (Ruy Lopez main lines, Italian basics)\n\n**Milestone:** Solve 1000+ puzzles; know Bird main move orders confidently\n\n---\n\n### Month 2: Essential Endgames (Silman 1200-2000)\n**Opening Work:**\n- *Bird's Opening* LTR \u2014 Chapters 7\u201312 (Dutch reversed setups, f4-f5 attacks)\n- *1\u2026e5* Jones \u2014 Chapters 5\u20138 (Anti-Ruy systems, Giuoco Piano)\n- *Benko Gambit Blueprint* \u2014 Chapters 1\u20135 (main 5.b6 and 5.bxc6 lines)\n\n**Milestone:** Reliably convert K+R+P vs K+R; understand Lucena & Philidor positions\n\n---\n\n### Month 3: The Calculation Bridge (Can Kabadayi Foundations)\n**Opening Work:**\n- *1\u2026e5* Jones LTR \u2014 Chapters 1\u20133 (Giuoco Piano & basics)\n- *Benko Gambit Blueprint* \u2014 Chapters 1\u20133 (Foundations)\n\n**Milestone:** Complete Levels 1-2; establish a rigid \"Candidate Move\" checklist before calculating.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2 \u2014 Structural Understanding (Months 4\u20136)\n\n### Month 4: Strategic Structures (Chess Structures - Nielsen Video)\n**Opening Refinement:**\n- *1\u2026e5* Jones \u2014 finish remaining chapters, focus on Berlin and Anti-Berlin\n- *Reversed Sicilian* Neiksans \u2014 Chapters 7\u201312 (fianchetto and Botvinnik setups)\n- Annotate 5+ of your own Bird games this month\n\n**Milestone:** Identify on sight which structure is on the board and name the correct plan\n\n---\n\n### Month 5: Tactical Volume II (Woodpecker Medium Focus)\n**Opening Work:**\n- Deep dive: *Bird's Opening* \u2014 rare sidelines, 1.f4 c5 (reversed Sicilian positions from White's side)\n- Play 15 rated OTB/classical online games \u2014 all with repertoire openings\n- Annotate every game focusing on **tactics you missed**\n\n**Milestone:** Pattern recognition noticeably faster; blunder rate drops in games\n\n---\n\n### Month 6: Strategic Imbalances (Silman Reassess - Video Focus)\n**Endgame Supplement:** *Silman's Complete Endgame Course* \u2014 2000\u20132200 section\n- Rook + pawn structures, opposite-colored bishops\n\n**Milestone:** Write a post-game imbalance analysis for 8+ of your games this month\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3 \u2014 Master-Level Thinking (Months 7\u20139)\n\n### Month 7: High-Level Piece Coordination (Kabadayi Coordination Trilogy)\n**Opening Refinement:**\n- Research key Benko Gambit theoretical novelties (use database: Lichess/ChessBase)\n- Start building your own **repertoire database** (ChessBase or Lichess studies)\n\n**Milestone:** Able to articulate the strategic theme of every game studied; repertoire database \u2265 300 annotated positions\n\n---\n\n### Month 8: Technical Threshold (Dvoretsky Endgame Manual)\n**Opening Work:**\n- Analyze your personal game database for opening problems\n- Patch weak spots in Bird (if opponent plays 1\u2026e5 Lasker variation, etc.)\n\n**Milestone:** Convert theoretically won rook endings consistently; DEM exercises \u2265 70% correct\n\n---\n\n### Month 9: Elite Thinking Process (GM Ramesh RB Calculation)\n**Opening Prep:**\n- Full opening study refresh: print/export all repertoire lines; test yourself without the board\n- Identify **3 critical novelties** in each of your 4 opening systems\n\n**Milestone:** Regularly solve 2400\u20132500-rated puzzles; opening prep is now airtight\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4 \u2014 Tournament Readiness (Months 10\u201312)\n\n### Month 10: Positional Depth (Gelfand Positional Decision Making)\n**Game Analysis:**\n- Analyze 10 of your recent games with **no engine first**, then compare with engine\n- Write a paragraph per game: \"What I missed and why\"\n\n**Milestone:** Your annotations match engine suggestions \u2265 50% of the time at critical moments\n\n---\n\n### Month 11: Repertoire Mastery (Bird/1...e5/Benko Sharpness)\n**Action Items:**\n- Memorize all critical forced lines in Bird and Benko to at least move 20\n- Study recent (2023\u20132025) GM games with your openings via database\n- Enter 1\u20132 OTB tournaments this month; treat them as training\n\n**Milestone:** In at least 80% of games, you reach a known position by move 12+ with confidence\n\n---\n\n### Month 12: Tournament Summit (Axel Smith + Boris Gelfand Capstone)\n**Milestone**: Compete in a FIDE event; achieve IM-level (2300-2400) performance.\n\n---\n\n## Weekly Training Template\n\n| Session | Hours/Week |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| Tactics (puzzles + Woodpecker) | 10 |\n| Calculation (Aagaard exercises) | 6 |\n| Endgames | 5 |\n| Openings (study + database work) | 4 |\n| Playing + deep game analysis | 10 |\n| **Total** | **\u2248 35 hrs** |\n\n---\n\n## Rating Milestones\n\n| Timeframe | Expected Rating |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| Month 3 | ~1900\u20131950 |\n| Month 6 | ~2050\u20132150 |\n| Month 9 | ~2200\u20132300 |\n| Month 12 | ~2350\u20132400 |\n\n---\n\n## Critical Principles\n\n1. **Your games are the #1 study material.** Every loss is a free lesson.\n2. **Never study openings without understanding the resulting middlegame structure.**\n3. **Tactics are never \"done.\"** Maintain 30+ min/day every month.\n4. **Quality over quantity.** One fully understood position > ten skimmed chapters.\n5. **Tournament discipline matters as much as home study at 2200+.**\n", "chess_mastery_reference": "# \u265f\ufe0f Chess Mastery Deep Reference Guide\n\n---\n\n## SECTION 1 \u2014 Board Visualization: The Hidden Foundation\n\n### Training the Whole Board: A Progressive Drill System\n\n**Week 1\u20132 \u2014 Square Color Recognition (5 min/day)**\n- Pick a random square (e.g., \"g5\") and instantly say its color without counting\n- Tool: [lichess.org/training/vision](https://lichess.org/training) \u2192 Board Vision mode\n\n**Week 3\u20134 \u2014 File & Rank Vision (10 min/day)**\n- Exercise: \"Rook sweep\" \u2014 mentally trace a rook from a1 to h1, name every square it crosses\n\n**Week 5\u20136 \u2014 Diagonal Vision (10 min/day)**\n- Know the two diagonals of every square like you know your phone number\n- Critical diagonals: **a2\u2013g8, b1\u2013h7, a1\u2013h8, h1\u2013a8**\n\n**Week 7\u20138 \u2014 Knight Sight (15 min/day)**\n1. **Touching Squares Drill**: Place knight on any square \u2192 name all squares it can reach\n2. **Two-Move Knight Vision**: See all squares a knight reaches in TWO jumps\n3. **Knight Pathfinding**: Fast routes across the board (e.g., a1 to h8)\n\n**Week 9\u201312 \u2014 Integration Training**\n- Solve 3 puzzles per day **on paper only, without a board**\n\n---\n\n## SECTION 2 \u2014 Calculation: What to Calculate & What to Ignore\n\n### The CCT Framework (Your First Filter)\n| Letter | Type | Why it matters |\n|--------|------|---------------|\n| **C** | Checks | Limits opponent responses dramatically |\n| **C** | Captures | Changes material balance |\n| **T** | Threats | Moves that create a threat winning material or mating |\n\n### The 3-Level Calculation System\n**Level 1 \u2014 Immediate Threats (Always, every move)**\n**Level 2 \u2014 Forced Lines (When there's tension)**\n**Level 3 \u2014 Strategic Assessment (No immediate tactics)**\n\n---\n\n## SECTION 3 \u2014 Deep Course & Book Research\n\n### \ud83c\udfaf Tactics & Pattern Recognition\n- **The Woodpecker Method** (Smith/Tikkanen) \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\n- **Forcing Chess Moves** (Hertan) \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\n\n### \ud83e\uddee Calculation Training\n- **Calculation** \u2014 Jacob Aagaard \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\n- **Improve Your Chess Calculation** \u2014 Ramesh RB \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\n\n### \ud83c\udfc1 Endgames\n- **100 Endgames You Must Know** \u2014 de la Villa \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\n- **Silman's Complete Endgame Course** \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\n- **Dvoretsky's Endgame Manual** \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\n\n### \ud83c\udfdb\ufe0f Positional Chess & Strategy\n- **How to Reassess Your Chess** \u2014 Silman \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\n- **Chess Structures: A Grandmaster Guide** \u2014 Flores Rios \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\n- **Positional Decision Making in Chess** \u2014 Gelfand \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\n\n---\n\n## SECTION 4 \u2014 The Weekly Checklist\n- [ ] Am I analyzing my own games?\n- [ ] Did I spend 30+ min on tactics today?\n- [ ] Am I calculated on paper (not just in my head) for hard positions?\n- [ ] Did I use the engine LAST?\n- [ ] Is my Chessable daily review streak maintained?\n\n### Quick Reference: Daily Routine\n| Block | Time | Activity |\n|-------|------|----------|\n| **PRIMARY** | 90\u2013120 min | Current month's main course |\n| **Tactics** | 45 min | Lichess puzzles or Woodpecker |\n| **Opening review** | 30 min | Chessable spaced repetition only |\n| **Endgame drill** | 20 min | Lichess Practice |\n| **Play + analyze** | 90 min | 1 game + self-annotation before engine |\n", "daily_training_system": "# \u265f\ufe0f 12-Month Daily Training System\n## One Focus Per Month. Everything Else = Maintenance Only.\n\n---\n\n## How The System Works\n\nEvery month has **ONE PRIMARY BLOCK** (90\u2013120 min/day).\nEverything else is a **fixed maintenance dose** \u2014 same time, same task, every day.\nYou do not add new courses mid-month. You do not skip days.\n\n**Daily session structure (~5 hrs/day = 35 hrs/week):**\n\n| Block | Time | Changes each month? |\n|-------|------|-------------------|\n| **PRIMARY** (monthly main course) | 90 min (120 min in Months 3, 9) | \u2705 Rotates monthly |\n| **Tactics** | 45 min | \u274c Never skipped |\n| **Visualization Ritual** (Lichess Score 30+) | 15 min | \u274c **High Intensity Warmup** |\n| **Opening review** | 30 min | \u274c Spaced rep only |\n| **Endgame Pillar** (Hellsten/Dvoretsky) | 20 min | \u274c **Year-Long Mastery** |\n| **Game play + deep self-analysis** | 90 min | \u274c Fixed |\n\n> [!IMPORTANT]\n> **The 3D Rule**: For all study blocks above, you MUST use a **physical chess set**. Do not solve puzzles on the screen. Look at the diagram, calculate *everything* while looking at the physical board, then play the moves. This is the only way to kill \"Board Blindness.\"\n\n> [!IMPORTANT]\n> If you only have 2 hours: do **Tactics (45 min) + PRIMARY (75 min). Everything else waits.**\n> On tournament days: minimum 20 min tactics + 20 min opening review. Nothing else.\n\n---\n\n## Opening Introduction Schedule (Strict \u2014 Do Not Deviate)\n\n| Month | New Opening Chapters Introduced | Notes |\n|-------|--------------------------------|-------|\n| 1 | Bird's Opening LTR \u2014 Ch. 1\u20132 only | Spaced rep of these 2 chapters from day 3 onward |\n| 2 | Bird's Opening LTR \u2014 Ch. 3\u20136 | Adds to spaced rep queue |\n| 3 | 1\u2026e5 Jones LTR \u2014 Ch. 1\u20135 + Benko Blueprint Ch. 1\u20133 | Split: Week 1\u20132 Jones, Week 3\u20134 Benko |\n| 4 | Reversed Sicilian Neiksans \u2014 Ch. 1\u20136 | New study; all others on spaced rep only |\n| 5 | Bird's Opening LTR \u2014 Ch. 7\u201310 (sidelines) | Complete Bird repertoire |\n| 6 | 1\u2026e5 Jones LTR \u2014 Ch. 6\u201310 (Ruy Lopez main lines) | Completes Jones core |\n| 7 | Benko Blueprint Ch. 4\u20138 | Completes Benko |\n| 8 | 1\u2026e5 Jones \u2014 Anti-Berlin + Giuoco Piano remaining | Patches gaps |\n| 9 | Full repertoire review (no new chapters) | Rotate 7.5 min/system daily |\n| 10 | Reversed Sicilian Neiksans \u2014 Ch. 7\u201312 | Completes Neiksans |\n| 11 | All 4 systems: consolidation only (no new chapters) | Test & fix gaps |\n| 12 | No new opening study | Tournament preparation only |\n\n---\n\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n## MONTH 1 \u2014 TACTICAL FOUNDATION\n**Mission: Building the Combat Software**\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n\n### \ud83c\udfb4 [COURSE POSTER: THE WOODPECKER METHOD](https://www.chessable.com/the-woodpecker-method/course/10582/)\n| Field | Detail |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| **The Job** | **Solve all blunders & recognize tactical patterns instantly.** |\n| **Coach** | **GM Axel Smith & GM Hans Tikkanen** (Olympic Trainers) |\n| **Superpower** | **Tactical X-Ray Vision**: Instant recognition of motifs. |\n| **Stats** | 1,100+ Puzzles / High-Frequency Drill / 4.8/5 Rating |\n\n> [!TIP]\n> **Daily Routine**:\n> 1. **Tactics (45m)**: Woodpecker sets (3D board).\n> 2. **Warmup (15m)**: Lichess Coordinate Trainer (Score 30+).\n> 3. **Ninja Time**: Apply the \"3 Questions\" from **Tactic Ninja** to every puzzle.\n\n### \ud83c\udfc6 The Elite Reward: \"Tactical X-Ray Vision\"\nThe board becomes a web of **lines of force**. You don't \"calculate\" forks; you **see** them glowing.\n\n### \ud83c\udfaf Mission Motivation\n\"You are not just doing puzzles; you are installing 'Combat Software' into your brain.\"\n\n### Daily Schedule\n\n| Block | Time | Exact Task |\n|-------|------|-----------|\n| PRIMARY \u2014 Woodpecker | 90 min | Solve 40\u201360 puzzles (Easy Set). Write your time per puzzle. No skipping. |\n| **Tactics Technique: Ninja** | 45 min | **Week 1-2: ChessMood Tactic Ninja**. Learn the \"3 Questions\". **Week 3-4**: Lichess (1500-1900) applying the 3 Questions. |\n| Opening review | 30 min | Week 1: Study Bird Ch. 1\u20132 (new). Week 2\u20134: Spaced rep of Ch. 1\u20132 only. |\n| **Kabadayi: Preventing Blunders** | 20 min | Work through CLAMP checklist exercises. Apply CLAMP method during today's game. |\n| Play + analyze | 90 min | 1 classical game (45 min) + annotate without engine first (45 min) |\n\n> **Why Ninja + Woodpecker?** *Tactic Ninja* is your software (technique); *Woodpecker* is your hardware stress test (volume). Use the \"3 Questions\" from Ninja to solve your Woodpecker puzzles. This avoids \"guessing\" and builds real vision.\n\n> **Why Preventing Blunders here?** Won 2025 Course of Year + Best Tactics. The CLAMP method must become habit early \u2014 4 weeks of daily practice in Month 1 means it's automatic by Month 2.\n\n### Weekly Milestones\n- **Week 1:** Complete Tactic Ninja (Motifs 1-12) + Woodpecker Easy Set first pass. Bird Ch. 1\u20132 learned.\n- **Week 2:** Complete Tactic Ninja (Motifs 13-24) + Redo failed Easy Woodpecker puzzles.\n- **Week 3:** Complete Medium Set first pass using the \"3 Questions\" for every puzzle.\n- **Week 4:** Redo all failed Medium puzzles. Run through Easy set fast (aim: 2\u00d7 faster than Week 1).\n\n### \u2705 Move to Month 2 when:\nEasy puzzles \u226580% accuracy and you recognize the pattern within 30 seconds on re-attempts.\n\n---\n\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n## MONTH 2 \u2014 ESSENTIAL ENDGAMES\n**Mission: Mastering the Art of the Finish**\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n\n### \ud83c\udfb4 [COURSE POSTER: SILMAN'S ENDGAME COURSE](https://www.chessable.com/silmans-complete-endgame-course/course/87711/)\n| Field | Detail |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| **The Job** | **Never lose a winning endgame or draw a drawn one.** |\n| **Coach** | **IM Jeremy Silman** (The World's Best Teacher) |\n| **Superpower** | **The Closing Specialist**: Calmness under endgame pressure. |\n| **Stats** | 10h Video / 191 Puzzles / \"The Bible\" of Endgames |\n\n> [!TIP]\n> **Daily Routine**:\n> 1. **Primary (90m)**: Study one type (e.g., Lucena) + **Drill vs Stockfish**.\n> 2. **Endgame Pillar (20m)**: Permanent maintenance block.\n\n### \ud83c\udfc6 The Elite Reward: \"The Closing Specialist\"\nWhile others panic as pieces leave the board, you feel **total calm**. You know the win is guaranteed.\n\n### \ud83c\udfaf Mission Motivation\n\"Endgames are where ratings are truly stolen. This month, you stop being a dreamer and start being a closer.\"\n\n### Daily Schedule\n\n| Block | Time | Exact Task |\n|-------|------|-----------|\n| PRIMARY \u2014 Silman | 90 min | Read 1 endgame section. Set up position. Play it vs. Stockfish (level 1). Must be able to win/hold before next session. |\n| Tactics maintenance | 45 min | Lichess puzzles \u2014 1700\u20132000 rated |\n| Opening review | 30 min | Week 1\u20132: Study Bird Ch. 3\u20134 (new). Week 3\u20134: Study Bird Ch. 5\u20136 (new). |\n| Endgame drill | 20 min | Drill that day's specific Silman endgame position again |\n| Play + analyze | 90 min | Deliberately steer games toward endgames. Identify endgame errors in analysis. |\n\n### Weekly Milestones\n- **Week 1:** Silman 1200\u20131400 section done (K+P endings, basic king opposition). Bird Ch. 3\u20134 learned.\n- **Week 2:** Silman 1400\u20131600 done. Philidor & Lucena positions: can explain and execute both. Bird Ch. 5\u20136 learned.\n- **Week 3:** Silman 1600\u20131800 done (rook vs pawn, queen vs pawn). Bird Ch. 5\u20136 in spaced rep.\n- **Week 4:** Silman 1800\u20132000 done. Review all positions \u2014 test each one from memory.\n\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n## MONTH 3 \u2014 THE CALCULATION BRIDGE\n**Mission: Installing the 3-Ply Foundation**\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n\n### \ud83c\udfb4 [COURSE POSTER: FUNDAMENTAL CALCULATION](https://www.chessable.com/fundamental-chess-calculation-skills/course/175869/)\n| Field | Detail |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| **The Job** | **Eliminate all 1-move blunders and 'opponent's spite' checks.** |\n| **Coach** | **CM Can Kabadayi** (Cognitive Scientist) |\n| **Superpower** | **Iron Logic**: Blunder-proofing your short-range calculation. |\n| **Stats** | 8h Video / Voted Course of the Year 2023 / 5/5 Rating |\n\n> [!TIP]\n> **Daily Routine**:\n> 1. **Primary (120m)**: Verify every intuition with cold logic.\n> 2. **The 3D Rule**: Calculate *everything* on your physical board.\n\n### \ud83c\udfc6 The Elite Reward: \"The Iron Logic\"\nYou stop \"trusting\" luck and start **verifying** the truth.\n\n### \ud83c\udfaf Mission Motivation\n\"Calculation is the muscle of chess. We are building the core strength that wins games.\"\n\n### Daily Schedule\n\n| Block | Time | Exact Task |\n|-------|------|-----------|\n| PRIMARY \u2014 Fundamental Calc | 120 min | Write candidate moves on paper before calculating. |\n| Tactics maintenance | 45 min | Lichess puzzles \u2014 1800\u20132100 rated |\n| Opening review | 30 min | Week 1-2: Jones Ch. 1-3. Week 3-4: Benko Blueprint Ch. 1-3. |\n| Endgame drill | 20 min | Lichess practice endgame structures |\n| Play + analyze | 90 min | Deliberately calculate candidate moves for both sides. |\n\n### Weekly Milestones\n- **Week 1:** Levels 1-2 completed. Jones Ch. 1-3 learned.\n- **Week 2:** Level 3 completed. Establish \"Candidate Move\" checklist.\n- **Week 3:** Level 4 completed. Benko Ch. 1-3 learned.\n- **Week 4:** Redo failed L1/L2 exercises. Test \"Thought Process\" checklist in 5 games.\n\n### \u2705 Move to Month 4 when:\nYou no longer \"blunder\" in simple 2-move calculations and can list 3+ candidate moves for any complex position.\n\n---\n\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n## MONTH 4 \u2014 STRATEGIC STRUCTURES\n**Mission: Decoding the Master's Blueprint**\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n\n### \ud83c\udfb4 [COURSE POSTER: CHESS STRUCTURES - GM GUIDE](https://www.chessable.com/chess-structures-a-grandmaster-guide/course/13155/)\n| Field | Detail |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| **The Job** | **Look at any pawn structure and know the next 15 moves.** |\n| **Coach** | **GM Peter Heine Nielsen** (Coach of Magnus Carlsen) |\n| **Superpower** | **Grandmaster Intuition**: Instant recognition of plans. |\n| **Stats** | 32h+ Video / 140 Model Games / 600+ Variations |\n\n> [!IMPORTANT]\n> **The Workflow**: Watch the **PHN Video** first. He gives the 'Why'. Then study the MoveTrainer variations for the 'How'.\n\n### \ud83c\udfc6 The Elite Reward: \"Grandmaster Intuition\"\nWelcome to the elite mindset. You no longer \"guess\"\u2014you **recognize**.\n\n### \ud83c\udfaf Mission Motivation\n\"You are studying the same secret blueprints that Magnus Carlsen used to dominate the world.\"\n\n**Core rule:** Watch the **PHN Video** for each structure *before* studying the variations. He gives the 'Why' that makes the 'How' easy.\n\n**Core rule:** After each structure chapter, find 2 master games with that structure in a database and guess every move.\n\n### Daily Schedule\n\n| Block | Time | Exact Task |\n|-------|------|-----------|\n| PRIMARY \u2014 Chess Structures | 90 min | Read 1 structure chapter + find 1 master game with that structure in Lichess database. Guess moves. |\n| Tactics maintenance | 45 min | Lichess puzzles \u2014 maintain 2000+ puzzle rating |\n| **Kabadayi: The Value of Pawns** | 30 min | Study 1 chapter on Chessable. Focus on evaluation of material vs quality vs time. |\n| Endgame drill | 20 min | Lichess Practice \u2192 Opposite-color bishop endings |\n| Play + analyze | 90 min | After each game: name the structure AND evaluate if your pawn trades were correct. |\n\n> **Note:** *The Value of Pawns* (Kabadayi) replaces the opening review slot for this month. It reinforces the positional concepts of *Chess Structures* with interactive training. Opening review should be limited to 5-10 min rapid check of spaced rep.\n\n### Weekly Milestones\n- **Week 1:** Stonewall, IQP, Carlsbad structures done. Neiksans Ch. 1\u20133 learned.\n- **Week 2:** Benko structure, Benoni done. Neiksans Ch. 4\u20136 learned.\n- **Week 3:** French, Sicilian, King's Indian structures done. You can name the plan within 10 sec in any studied structure.\n- **Week 4:** Review all structures. Annotate 3 of your Bird games identifying the structure and whether your plan was correct.\n\n### \u2705 Move to Month 5 when:\nGiven any position in a structure you've studied, you name the correct plan for both sides without pausing.\n\n---\n\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n## MONTH 5 \u2014 TACTICAL VOLUME II (Speed)\n**Mission: Achieving Blitz-Like Processing**\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n\n### \ud83c\udfb4 [COURSE POSTER: WOODPECKER CYCLE 2](https://www.chessable.com/the-woodpecker-method/course/10582/)\n| Field | Detail |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| **The Job** | **Solve the same 1,100 puzzles 30% faster than Month 1.** |\n| **Coach** | **GM Axel Smith** (Rating Specialist) |\n| **Superpower** | **The Blitz Mind**: Doubling your calculation speed. |\n| **Stats** | High-Intensity Speed Repetition / Tracking Time vs Month 1 |\n\n> [!TIP]\n> **Daily Routine**:\n> 1. **Primary (90m)**: Speed puzzles (3D board).\n> 2. **Maintenance**: Opening review (30m).\n\n### \ud83c\udfc6 The Elite Reward: \"The Blitz Mind\"\nYou save 30\u201340 minutes on the clock because you see the basics instantly.\n\n### \ud83c\udfaf Mission Motivation\n\"Speed is the final signature of mastery. This month, you become a bullet on the board.\"\n\n**Core rule:** Same puzzles, much faster. Track every session time. Aim for 30\u201340% speed improvement vs. Month 1.\n\n### Daily Schedule\n\n| Block | Time | Exact Task |\n|-------|------|-----------|\n| PRIMARY \u2014 Woodpecker Cycle 2 | 90 min | 80\u2013100 puzzles per session. Easy set target: done in \u226445 min. Medium set target: done in \u226445 min. |\n| Tactics maintenance | 45 min | Lichess \u2014 theme-filtered (rotate weekly: pins \u2192 forks \u2192 discovered attacks \u2192 skewers) |\n| Opening review | 30 min | Week 1\u20132: Bird's Opening Ch. 7\u20138 (sidelines, new). Week 3\u20134: Bird Ch. 9\u201310 (new). |\n| Endgame drill | 20 min | Lichess Practice \u2192 Rook + Pawn vs Rook (Philidor and Lucena again, timed) |\n| Play + analyze | 90 min | Play 15 rated games this month. Every game annotated. Find the tactical miss in each. |\n\n### Weekly Milestones\n- **Week 1:** Easy set completed in \u226445 min (vs ~90 min in Month 1). Bird sidelines Ch. 7\u20138 learned.\n- **Week 2:** Medium set \u226585% accuracy. Bird Ch. 9\u201310 learned \u2014 Bird repertoire now complete.\n- **Week 3:** Both Easy + Medium completed in one 90-min session.\n- **Week 4:** Redo all incorrect puzzles from the entire Woodpecker set.\n\n### \u2705 Move to Month 6 when:\nPattern recognition is visibly faster in games. Blunder rate in annotated games measurably lower than Month 1.\n\n---\n\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n## MONTH 6 \u2014 STRATEGIC IMBALANCES\n**Mission: Engineering the Winning Advantage**\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n\n### \ud83c\udfb4 [COURSE POSTER: REASSESS YOUR CHESS](https://www.chessable.com/how-to-reassess-your-chess/course/87710/)\n| Field | Detail |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| **The Job** | **Formulate a grand strategy based on positional imbalances.** |\n| **Coach** | **IM Jeremy Silman** (Video: GM Maurice Ashley) |\n| **Superpower** | **The Architect's Vision**: Seeing imbalances others miss. |\n| **Stats** | 23.5h Video / 4.7/5 Rating / The Core Strategy System |\n\n### \ud83c\udfc6 The Elite Reward: \"The Architect's Vision\"\nYou stop playing moves and start building **masterpieces**.\n\n### \ud83c\udfaf Mission Motivation\n\"Strategy is the art of the possible. Turn any small advantage into a crushing victory.\"\n\n**Core rule:** Read one imbalance chapter. Find 2 master games illustrating that imbalance. Apply it to your next game. No chapter-skipping.\n\n### Daily Schedule\n\n| Block | Time | Exact Task |\n|-------|------|-----------|\n| PRIMARY \u2014 Silman Reassess | 90 min | 1 chapter \u2192 identify the imbalance \u2192 find 2 master games from Lichess database showing it. |\n| Tactics maintenance | 45 min | Chess Tempo \u2014 rated 1800\u20132200, timed mode |\n| Opening review | 30 min | Week 1\u20132: Jones 1\u2026e5 Ch. 4\u20136 (new). Week 3\u20134: Jones Ch. 7\u201310 (new). |\n| **Kabadayi: Chess Crime and Punishment** | 20 min | Study 1 chapter. Focus on spotting positional errors your opponents make. |\n| Play + analyze | 90 min | After each game: identify 1 positional \"crime\" committed by either side. |\n\n> **Note:** *Chess Crime and Punishment* replaces the endgame drill slot for this month to deepen positional intuition alongside Silman.\n\n### Weekly Milestones\n- **Week 1:** Weak squares, open files chapters done. Jones Ch. 4\u20136 learned.\n- **Week 2:** Bishops vs knights, pawn majority chapters done. Jones Ch. 7\u201310 \u2014 Jones repertoire now complete.\n- **Week 3:** King safety, unbalanced positions done. Write your personal \"Imbalance Checklist\" (1 page).\n- **Week 4:** Apply checklist to last 5 of your own games. Identify which imbalance you mishandle most often.\n\n### \u2705 Move to Month 7 when:\nYou can name all 7 Silman imbalances and correctly label them in post-game analysis.\n\n---\n\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n## MONTH 7 \u2014 PIECE COORDINATION\n**Mission: Orchestrating the Full Attack**\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n\n### \ud83c\udfb4 [COURSE POSTER: ART OF COORDINATION](https://www.chessable.com/the-art-of-awakening-pieces/course/136015/)\n| Field | Detail |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| **The Job** | **Find the perfect square for every piece on the board.** |\n| **Coach** | **CM Can Kabadayi** (FIDE Trainer) |\n| **Superpower** | **The Harmony Specialist**: Awakening sleeping pieces. |\n| **Stats** | 3 Courses (Burying / Awakening / Exchanging) |\n\n### \ud83c\udfc6 The Elite Reward: \"The Harmony Specialist\"\nYou see the board as an **orchestra**. You know exactly which piece is \"out of tune.\"\n\n### \ud83c\udfaf Mission Motivation\n\"A piece is only as good as its coordination. Learn the secret language of the pieces.\"\n\n**Core rule:** These three courses form a complete system for piece coordination. Study them in order: Burying \u2192 Awakening \u2192 Exchanging. Each chapter: study the concept, find 1 master game demonstrating it, then test yourself in the play session.\n\n### Daily Schedule\n\n| Block | Time | Exact Task |\n|-------|------|-----------|\n| Session 1 (90 min) | **PRIMARY \u2014 Kabadayi Trilogy** | Week 1\u20132: Art of Burying Pieces. Week 3: Art of Awakening Pieces. Week 4: Art of Exchanging Pieces. |\n| Session 2 (45 min) | Tactics maintenance | Lichess puzzles \u2014 push to 2100\u20132300 range |\n| Session 3 (30 min) | Opening \u2014 Chessable | Week 1\u20132: Benko Blueprint Ch. 4\u20136 (new). Week 3\u20134: Benko Ch. 7\u20138 (new). |\n| Session 4 (20 min) | Endgame drill | Lichess Practice \u2192 must-know rook endings (timed test from memory) |\n| Session 5 (90 min) | Play + Zurich 1953 | Play 1 game (50 min). Then: guess-the-move through a Zurich 1953 position for 40 min. |\n\n> **Why this swap?** Zurich 1953 is passive book study. The Kabadayi trilogy is interactive Chessable training on precisely the hardest skill gap at your level: piece coordination. Zurich 1953 is now supplementary in Session 5.\n\n### Weekly Milestones\n- **Week 1:** Art of Burying Pieces completed. Benko Ch. 4\u20136 learned.\n- **Week 2:** Art of Burying MoveTrainer review done. Start Awakening Pieces. Benko Ch. 7\u20138 learned.\n- **Week 3:** Art of Awakening Pieces completed. Study 4 games from Zurich 1953 in Session 5.\n- **Week 4:** Art of Exchanging Pieces completed. Explaining tradeoff logic for all trades.\n\n### \u2705 Move to Month 8 when:\nYou can look at any position and instantly identify which piece is \"sleeping\" or \"buried\" and how to exchange to fix it.\n\n---\n\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n## MONTH 8 \u2014 ENDGAME MASTERY (PROFESSIONAL)\n**Mission: Entering the Top 1%**\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n\n### \ud83c\udfb4 [COURSE POSTER: DVORETSKY'S MANUAL](https://www.chessable.com/dvoretskys-endgame-manual-5th-edition/course/43048/)\n| Field | Detail |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| **The Job** | **Memorize the critical theoretical endings for master play.** |\n| **Coach** | **GM Karsten M\u00fcller & GM Erwin L'Ami** |\n| **Superpower** | **The Professional Threshold**: Perfect technique from memory. |\n| **Stats** | 24h Video / 800+ Variations / The Endgame Bible |\n\n### \ud83c\udfc6 The Elite Reward: \"The Professional Threshold\"\nBy surviving Dvoretsky, you enter the **1% of chess players**.\n\n### \ud83c\udfaf Mission Motivation\n\"This is the filter that separates masters from amateurs. Stay disciplined.\"\n\n**Core rule:** Study rook endings first (most common in practice). Verify every position with Syzygy tablebases at lichess.org/analysis. Drill each position vs. Stockfish from both sides before moving on.\n\n### Daily Schedule\n\n| Block | Time | Exact Task |\n|-------|------|-----------|\n| PRIMARY \u2014 Dvoretsky | 90 min | Study 1 endgame section. Verify with Syzygy. Play it from both sides vs. Stockfish. Do not move to next section until you can win/hold reliably. |\n| Tactics maintenance | 45 min | Lichess puzzles (maintain 2200+ difficulty) |\n| Opening review | 30 min | Jones \u2014 Anti-Berlin + Giuoco Piano remaining chapter gaps (patch only, spaced rep rest) |\n| Endgame drill | 20 min | Drill that day's specific Dvoretsky position again |\n| Play + analyze | 90 min | Steer games toward endgames. Test Dvoretsky knowledge in real games. |\n\n### Weekly Milestones\n- **Week 1:** Rook + Pawn endings done: Lucena, Philidor, third-rank defense, Rook behind passed pawn. (Note: Saavedra is a queen study \u2014 it belongs in Week 3.)\n- **Week 2:** Pawn endings done: king opposition, triangulation, zugzwang, breakthrough.\n- **Week 3:** Queen endings + Saavedra position + minor piece endings (B vs N theoretical positions).\n- **Week 4:** Review all. Achieve 70%+ on 20 random Dvoretsky test positions chosen without preparation.\n\n### \u2705 Move to Month 9 when:\nYou convert theoretically won R+P endings against Stockfish with 90%+ consistency.\n\n---\n\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n## MONTH 9 \u2014 ELITE CALCULATION\n**Mission: The Grandmaster Bootcamp**\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n\n### \ud83c\udfb4 [COURSE POSTER: IMPROVE YOUR CHESS CALCULATION](https://www.chessable.com/improve-your-chess-calculation/course/149590/)\n| Field | Detail |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| **The Job** | **Deep variation stamina and candidate move discipline.** |\n| **Coach** | **GM Ramesh R.B.** (Coach of Praggnanandhaa) |\n| **Superpower** | **The Calculation Tank**: Surviving the tactical storm. |\n| **Stats** | 18h+ Video / 5 Levels / FIDE Approved |\n\n### \ud83c\udfc6 The Elite Reward: \"The Calculation Tank\"\nYou gain the **stamina** to calculate deep variations without \"lazy\" mistakes.\n\n### \ud83c\udfaf Mission Motivation\n\"This is your 'Grandmaster Bootcamp.' Every hour adds 10 FIDE points to your rating.\"\n\n**Core rule:** This is the hardest month. 2\u20133 exercises per session maximum. 20-minute timer per exercise. Do NOT look at solutions early. Redo wrong ones before doing new ones.\n\n### Daily Schedule\n\n| Block | Time | Exact Task |\n|-------|------|-----------|\n| PRIMARY \u2014 Aagaard GM Prep Calc | 120 min | 2\u20133 exercises only. Timer on. Write all variations. Compare with solution. Score yourself. |\n| Tactics maintenance | 45 min | Lichess \u2014 filter \"Long\" puzzles (4+ move solutions) only |\n| Opening review | 30 min | Full repertoire audit: rotate daily (7.5 min each system: Bird \u2192 Jones \u2192 Benko \u2192 Neiksans). Spaced rep only \u2014 no new chapters. |\n| Endgame drill | 20 min | Endgame studies on Lichess \u2014 2 studies per day (pure calculation training) |\n| Play + analyze | 90 min | After every game: find the position where calculation failed. Write the correct full line on paper. |\n\n### Weekly Milestones\n- **Week 1:** Chapters 1\u20133 done. Identify your calculation error pattern (missing defensive resources? losing the thread after 4 moves?).\n- **Week 2:** Chapters 4\u20136 done. Accuracy improving \u2014 even if speed is still slow, that's correct at this stage.\n- **Week 3:** Chapters 7\u20139 done. Redo all wrong exercises from Weeks 1\u20132.\n- **Week 4:** Final chapter + 10 random exercises under time pressure as a self-test.\n\n### \u2705 Move to Month 10 when:\nYou calculate 5\u20136 moves deep accurately without losing the thread in training positions.\n\n---\n\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n## MONTH 10 \u2014 GM THINKING PROCESS\n**Mission: Thinking Like a World Challenger**\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n\n### \ud83c\udfb4 [COURSE POSTER: POSITIONAL DECISION MAKING](https://www.chessable.com/positional-decision-making-in-chess/course/29329/)\n| Field | Detail |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| **The Job** | **Master the high-level language of prophylaxis and restriction.** |\n| **Coach** | **GM Boris Gelfand** (World Championship Challenger) |\n| **Superpower** | **The Gelfand Mindset**: Master-level positional sense. |\n| **Stats** | 278 Puzzles / High-Level Conversational Wisdom |\n\n### \ud83c\udfc6 The Elite Reward: \"The Gelfand Mindset\"\nYou stop reacting to your opponent and start **restricting** them.\n\n### \ud83c\udfaf Mission Motivation\n\"Learn the philosophy of a World Challenger. Stop thinking like a player, start thinking like a Master.\"\n\n**Core rule:** After each chapter, play 2 rated games and try to apply Gelfand's exact thinking process. Review those games against the chapter's framework the next day.\n\n### Daily Schedule\n\n| Block | Time | Exact Task |\n|-------|------|-----------|\n| PRIMARY \u2014 Gelfand | 90 min | Read 1 chapter. Find 2 current GM games (2023\u20132025 database) using the same concept. Replay them with guessing. |\n| Tactics maintenance | 45 min | Chess Tempo \u2014 2200\u20132500 rated problems |\n| **Kabadayi: Art of Multi-Purpose Moves** | 30 min | Study 1 chapter. Focus on moves that serve 2+ goals (attack/defend/improve position). |\n| Endgame drill | 20 min | Theoretical Rook Endgames (Shankland/Aagaard) \u2014 1 section per day, verify with tablebases |\n| Play + analyze | 90 min | Engine goes LAST. Write full annotation first. Note: which of your moves served multiple purposes? |\n\n> **Note:** *Art of Multi-Purpose Moves* (Kabadayi) replaces the opening review slot for this month to bridge the gap between Gelfand's theory and concrete move selection.\n\n### Weekly Milestones\n- **Week 1\u20132:** Prophylaxis, piece activity, restricting opponent \u2014 apply in 4 games. Neiksans Ch. 7\u20139 learned.\n- **Week 3:** Static vs. dynamic play chapter \u2014 applies directly to Bird's Opening philosophy. Neiksans Ch. 10\u201312 done \u2014 Neiksans repertoire complete.\n- **Week 4:** Annotate 5 of your own games using Gelfand's decision checklist explicitly.\n\n### \u2705 Move to Month 11 when:\nYour own pre-engine annotations match engine top choices \u226550% of the time at critical decision moments.\n\n---\n\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n## MONTH 11 \u2014 REPERTOIRE MASTERY\n**Mission: The Opening Specialist**\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n\n### \ud83c\udfb4 REPERTOIRE POSTER: BIRD / 1...E5 / BENKO\n| Field | Detail |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| **The Job** | **Lock in move-20 mastery for all 4 primary systems.** |\n| **Systems** | Bird (Colovic/Banzea), 1...e5 (Jones), Benko (Blueprint) |\n| **Superpower** | **The Opening Specialist**: Unshakeable move-1 confidence. |\n\n### \ud83c\udfc6 The Elite Reward: \"The Opening Specialist\"\nYou walk to the board knowing you are better prepared than 99% of your opponents.\n\n### \ud83c\udfaf Mission Motivation\n\"Consistency is the final step to 2400. Polish the sword for the final battle.\"\n\n**Core rule:** NO new opening material. Test every line in actual games. Fix any gap found before studying the next system.\n\n### Daily Schedule\n\n| Block | Time | Exact Task |\n|-------|------|-----------|\n| PRIMARY \u2014 Repertoire Test | 90 min | Day 1\u20137: Bird's Opening \u2014 test all lines without hints; patch gaps. Day 8\u201314: Jones 1\u2026e5 \u2014 same. Day 15\u201321: Benko Blueprint \u2014 same. Day 22\u201328: Reversed Sicilian \u2014 same. |\n| Tactics maintenance | 45 min | Lichess puzzles \u2014 2200+ range (maintain sharpness) |\n| Database work | 30 min | Find 5 recent GM games per week with your opening. Import to Lichess Study. Note any lines you haven't seen. |\n| Endgame drill | 20 min | Random Dvoretsky positions \u2014 test yourself without preparation |\n| Play + analyze | 90 min | OTB or long online (30+30 min) games. Only play your repertoire. Annotate same day. |\n\n### Weekly Milestones\n- **Week 1:** Bird test \u2014 can you play all main lines to move 15 without a board? Any gap found = fix it in the PRIMARY block that day.\n- **Week 2:** Jones 1\u2026e5 test \u2014 same standard. Patches done in primary block.\n- **Week 3:** Benko + Reversed Sicilian test \u2014 same standard. All 4 systems now at \u2265 move 12 confident depth.\n- **Week 4:** Enter a tournament (OTB or online classical). Every opening problem found = fixed same week.\n\n### \u2705 Move to Month 12 when:\nIn 80%+ of games you reach a known, comfortable position by move 12.\n\n---\n\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n## MONTH 12 \u2014 TOURNAMENT SUMMIT: THE ELITE CAPSTONE\n**Mission: The Breakthrough & Professional Performance**\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n\n### \ud83c\udfb4 [FINAL BOSS POSTER: THE PERFORMANCE DUAL-SYSTEM](https://www.chessable.com/pump-up-your-rating/course/24430/)\n| Field | Detail |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| **The Job** | **Peak your tactical and positional state for tournament play.** |\n| **Coaches** | **GM Axel Smith** + **GM Boris Gelfand** |\n| **Superpower** | **The Universal Playing Style**: Total mastery across all phases. |\n\n### \ud83c\udfc6 The Elite Reward: \"The Breakthrough\"\nThis is the moment everything comes together. You are no longer \"studying\"\u2014you are **dominating**.\n\n### \ud83c\udfaf Mission Motivation\n\"Look back at the person you were 12 months ago. You are no longer a club player. Claim your 2400-FIDE territory.\"\n\n**Core rule:** Compete. All study serves the tournament. \n- **Axel Smith**: Study the \"List of Mistakes\" and \"9-Point Calculation\" chapters daily.\n- **Boris Gelfand**: Solve 3 \"Dynamic Decision\" problems every morning after your visualization ritual.\n\n### Daily Schedule\n\n| Block | Time | Exact Task |\n|-------|------|-----------|\n| PRIMARY \u2014 Pump Up Your Rating | 60 min | Read 1 chapter. Write 1 concrete change to your tournament routine it recommends. Apply it this week. |\n| Tactics maintenance | 45 min | Lichess puzzles \u2014 maintain sharpness (pattern maintenance only) |\n| Opponent preparation | 30 min | Run upcoming opponents' games through database. Find their opening preferences and tactical weaknesses. |\n| Visualization drill | 20 min | Knight pathfinding + long diagonal drills (keep board vision sharp before rounds) |\n| Tournament play | 90\u2013120 min | Play FIDE-rated events. After rounds: rest. Annotate next morning (engine last). |\n\n### Tournament Day Protocol\n1. Morning: 15-min light opening review only (no new chapters, no deep calculation)\n2. 30 min before game: short walk, no chess\n3. During game: CCT scan every 5 moves; write your remaining clock time\n4. Post-game: Annotate without engine before sleep; engine check next morning\n\n### Weekly Milestones\n- **Week 1:** Read all of *Pump Up Your Rating*. Write personal \"Pre-Tournament Checklist\" (1 page).\n- **Week 2\u20134:** FIDE-rated tournament(s). Apply everything. Every game gets full annotation.\n\n---\n\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n## Hard Rules \u2014 Never Break These\n## \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n\n1. **One primary course per month. Complete it. Do not jump to next month's course early.**\n2. **Tactics every single day \u2014 45 min minimum. On tournament days: 20 min minimum. Never zero.**\n3. **Opening review = Chessable spaced repetition only, unless the month's schedule explicitly introduces new chapters.**\n4. **Engine goes LAST in all game analysis. Your own written analysis first, always.**\n5. **Do not buy or start any new course not in this plan before finishing the current month's primary course.**\n6. **Re-read the weekly checklist in the Reference Guide every Sunday.**\n", "training_philosophy": "# Training Philosophy & Rationale: The Road to 2400\n\nUnderstanding the \"Why\" is the difference between blindly following a list and actually transforming your chess. This document explains the pedagogical logic behind the **Elite Hybrid Plan (2026)**.\n\n## 1. The \"Software vs. Hardware\" Principle\n**Core Idea:** You cannot run high-level chess software (calculation) on broken hardware (tactical blindness).\n\n*   **Tactic Ninja (The Software):** We start with this in Month 1 because it teaches you *how to look* at a board. It installs the \"3-Question Algorithm\" in your brain. Without this, Woodpecker is just guessing; with this, Woodpecker is *refining*.\n*   **The Woodpecker Method (The Hardware):** This provides the volume needed for subconscious pattern recognition. At 2100+, you don't calculate a skewer\u2014you \"see\" it as a color. This requires the thousands of reps you do here.\n\n## 2. The \"Process Before Depth\" Principle\n**Core Idea:** Efficiency in calculation comes from *where* you look, not just *how far* you look.\n\n*   **Ramesh RB (The Process - Month 3):** Most 2000-rated players fail calculation because they miss the \"candidate move\" on move 1. Ramesh\u2019s method forces you to find candidate moves for *both* sides first. This fixes the \"blind spot\" issue.\n*   **Jacob Aagaard (The Depth - Month 9):** Once your process is clean, you need to extend your stamina. Aagaard\u2019s positions are \"brutally deep.\" You only do this after Ramesh has taught you *not* to miss the simple move.\n\n## 3. The \"Interactive Mastery\" Principle\n**Core Idea:** Passive reading is a lie; only active solving builds permanent neurons.\n\n*   **Kabadayi Art Trilogy (The Piece Logic - Month 7):** Positionally, the hardest gap at 2000 elo is \"Piece Coordination\"\u2014making your pieces talk to each other. We moved Zurich 1953 (passive book reading) to a supplement and made Kabadayi primary because Chessable\u2019s MoveTrainer forces you to solve coordination problems daily.\n*   **Value of Pawns / Crime & Punishment:** These are placed alongside structural books (Flores Rios/Silman) to provide immediate, solvable examples of the abstract theory you just read.\n\n## 4. The Repertoire Efficiency Logic\n**Core Idea:** Every hour spent on opening memorization is an hour stolen from calculation training.\n\n*   **Why Bird's (1.f4)?** Because it is a \"System\" that 95% of your opponents haven't studied deeply. It allows you to reach a middlegame you understand (Stonewall/Lasker structures) without having to know 30 moves of Najdorf or Berlin theory. \n*   **Strategic Consistency:** The Bird (White) and the Reversed Sicilian (Black) share similar structural DNA, making your \"pattern database\" more efficient.\n\n## 5. Summary of Synergies\n- **Month 1-2**: Technique (Ninja) \u2192 Volume (Woodpecker) \u2192 Safety (Kabadayi Blunders).\n- **Month 3-5**: Process (Ramesh) \u2192 Structural Plans (Flores) \u2192 Result Conversion (Games).\n- **Month 6-10**: Positional Imbalance (Grooten) \u2192 Coordination (Kabadayi) \u2192 Elite Decision Making (Gelfand).\n\n## 6. The \"Endgame Guarantee\" Principle\n**Core Idea:** You cannot reach 2400 if you fear the endgame. 2000s lose to IMs because they play for the attack to *avoid* the ending; IMs win because they steer into the ending they know they can outplay you in.\n*   **The Daily Pillar**: We have added a permanent 20-minute \"Endgame Guarantee\" to every single month. By the end of the year, you will have over 100 hours of *pure* endgame technique, making you the \"fear\" of your local tournament circuit.\n\n## 7. The \"Square Fluency\" Principle (Visualization)\n**Core Idea:** Board blindness is a \"loading error\" in your brain. If your brain is struggling to remember where the f6 knight is, it has no energy left to calculate a sacrifice.\n*   **The 2D vs 3D Gap**: Many players find online visualization \"easy\" because the screen is a simplified 2D plane. OTB (3D) chess is cognitively harder. To fix this, we use the **3D Rule**.\n*   **The 3D Rule**: You MUST solve puzzles and courses while looking at a physical board (not the screen).\n*   **Cognitive Loading**: By solving from a diagram *away* from the board, you force your brain to build its own internal \"3D engine.\" This is the only way to reach 2400.\n\n## 8. The \"Strategic Imbalance\" Principle (Strategy)\n**Core Idea:** Strategy isn't just \"having a plan.\" It's recognizing the **Imbalances** (as taught by Jeremy Silman).\n*   **Silman Strategy (Video Focus)**: We take the \"Elite Hybrid\" approach here by combining your video ownership with active calculation. Watching the video provides the \"Wisdom,\" while your 3D Rule practice provides the \"Execution.\"\n*   **Planning vs. Guessing**: The goal is to move from \"reassessing\" the position as a passive activity to \"planning\" as a dynamic calculation based on imbalances.\n\n## 9. The \"Psychological Bridge\" Principle (Motivation)\n**Core Idea:** Improvement is rarely a straight line. Between Month 4 and Month 10, many players quit because they hit a \"Plateau.\"\n*   **The Positivity System**: The Command Center is designed to be your daily cheerleader. Instead of a grueling bootcamp, it provides clear daily tasks alongside the course poster and a direct link. \n*   **Daily Progression**: Check off your tasks every day. Hard work is difficult enough, so as you finish chapters and milestones, you'll be greeted with congratulations and positive quotes.\n*   **The Positive Feedback Loop**: Checking off daily tasks provides a visual, satisfying record of your consistency, giving you undeniable proof of your daily growth and an uplifting environment to train in.\n"};
